// Regression: when two namespaces declare a top-level type with the same bare
// name, importing one BY ALIAS and constructing it directly must resolve to the
// aliased namespace's type — not whichever same-named type appears first in
// compilation order. (a_acme.fc sorts before b_widget.fc, so acme's `point`
// registers first; the alias below targets widget's `point`.)
namespace acme::

struct point =
    x: i32
